The primary election conducted to elect the PDP candidate for the Udu/Ughelli Federal Constituency in the House of Representatives has been cancelled by the National Working Committee (NWC) of the party with a rerun ordered for the poll. A Statement issued by the Delta State Publicity Secretary of the party, Dr Ifeanyi Osuoza on Sunday disclosed that a rerun has been scheduled for Monday, May 30, 2022, at the Ughelli Township Stadium by 1 pm. Dr Osuoza did not give reasons for the cancellation but referred to a decision of the Appeal Committee of the party which sat over a petition concerning the election which earlier declared Hon. Talib Website as the winner. -Advertisement- The statement dated Sunday, May 29, 2022, stated as follows: “This is to notify all concerned Aspirants, Delegates, and party members, that the primaries, earlier conducted for the Udu/Ughelli Federal Constituency, has been cancelled by the National Working Committee, (NWC) of our party, as a result of a decision taken by the Appeals Committee. “A new date has now been fixed for the Re-run of the Primaries on Monday, May 30th, 2022 at Ughelli Township Stadium at 1 pm. “The following, concerning Delegates, Aspirants, Agents, Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), Security Agencies, and the Media should please take note”, the statement added.